Portland school board bans climate change-denying materials

Environmental groups say science is clear, so textbooks should be, too

In a move spearheaded by environmentalists, the Portland Public Schools board unanimously approved a resolution aimed at eliminating doubt of climate change and its causes in schools.

It is unacceptable that we have textbooks in our schools that spread doubt about the human causes and urgency of the crisis, said Lincoln High School student Gaby
